President Obama and President Hollande of France had a phone call regarding the use of chemical weapons by the Assad regime in Syria. They agreed that the international community should send a strong message that such crimes are unacceptable and those responsible will be held accountable. President Obama informed President Hollande that he has decided to take limited military action against the Syrian government and will seek authorization from Congress for the use of force. President Obama thanked President Hollande for France's commitment to upholding the international norm against chemical weapons and stated that they will continue to consult closely on Syria.